K-fold cross-validation

Loading data 

## Load commands
diamonds <- readr::read_rds("data/diamonds.rds")
register("diamonds")
## Load commands
dvd <- readr::read_rds("data/dvd.rds")
register("dvd")

Creating training variables 

## created variable to select training sample
dvd <- mutate(dvd, training = make_train(0.7, blocks = select(dvd, buy), seed = 1234))
## created variable to select training sample
diamonds <- mutate(diamonds, training = make_train(0.7, n(), seed = 1234))

Run a random forest and then update based on cross-validation 

result <- rforest(
  dvd, 
  rvar = "buy", 
  evar = c("coupon", "purch", "last"), 
  lev = "yes", 
  mtry = 1, 
  num.trees = 100,
  min.node.size = 100,
  data_filter = "training == 1",
  seed = 1234
)
summary(result)

Using a Gradient Boosted Treed for regression 

result <- gbt(
  diamonds, 
  rvar = "price", 
  evar = c("carat", "clarity", "cut", "color", "depth", "table"), 
  type = "regression", 
  max_depth = 3,
  learning_rate = 0.5,
  nrounds = 256,
  early_stopping_rounds = 3, 
  seed = 1234, 
  data_filter = "training == 1"
)
summary(result, prn = TRUE)
